    "body" : "<h2><code>assertArrayEquals</code> in JUnit 5 &amp; 6</h2>\n<p>In <a href=\"https://docs.junit.org/current/user-guide/#overview-what-is-junit-5\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><em>JUnit Jupiter</em></a>, we can use <a href=\"https://docs.junit.org/current/api/org.junit.jupiter.api/org/junit/jupiter/api/Assertions.html#assertArrayEquals(int%5B%5D,int%5B%5D)\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>Assertions.assertArrayEquals</code></a> method. Pass the <code>int</code> arrays.</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>import org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions;\n\nAssertions.assertArrayEquals(resultArray,actualResult);\n</code></pre>\n"
