  "title" : "Comparing arrays in JUnit assertions, concise built-in way?",
  "body" : "<p>Is there a concise, built-in way to do equals assertions on two like-typed arrays in JUnit?  By default (at least in JUnit 4) it seems to do an instance compare on the array object itself.</p>\n\n<p>EG, doesn't work:</p>\n\n<pre><code>int[] expectedResult = new int[] { 116800,  116800 };\nint[] result = new GraphixMask().sortedAreas(rectangles);\nassertEquals(expectedResult, result);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Of course, I can do it manually with:</p>\n\n<pre><code>assertEquals(expectedResult.length, result.length);\nfor (int i = 0; i &lt; expectedResult.length; i++)\n    assertEquals(\"mismatch at \" + i, expectedResult[i], result[i]);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>..but is there a better way?</p>\n"
